  "description": [
    "Kellogg Grant Enables GWU to Offer Short Courses for Doctors For doctors returning from the armed forces and civilian physi cians who may be Interested George Washington University In February will offer postgraduate courses In generalpractice and a number of specialties Dr Walter A Bloedorn dean of the School of Medicine an nounced last night The courses are made possible he said by a grant from the W K Kellogg Foundation of Battle Creek Mich to the university The size of the grant was not revealed The short intensive courses varying from one to nine weeks In length will be given at intervals between February l and April 13 The general review course will be presented at the School of Medicine 1335 H street NW and specialty courses will be given partly at the school and partly in various hos pitals in the city to be announced later Prominent guest physicians will supplement the medical faculty of the university Plans Longer Courses In addition to the intensive courses of instruction the School of Medicine also will offer longer period of Instruction in certain spe cialties Dr Bloedorn explained A series of preceptorships in the specitlties also will be offered The"
  ],
